[1
CLASSICAL SWINE FEVER IN GERMANY:
----------------------------------
Invalidation of the outbreak of Brandenburg
See also: 2 Nov 2001, 26 Oct 2001, 12 Oct 2001, 20 Jul 2001, 29 Jun 2001, 1
Sep 2000
Information received on 19 Oct 2001 from Prof. Dr Werner Zwingmann, Chief
Veterinary Officer, Ministry of Food, Agriculture and Forestry, Bonn:
Report date: 19 Oct 2001.
The declaration of a case of classical swine fever in Brandenburg Land (see
Disease Information, 14 [41, 233, dated 12 Oct 2001) was due to a
false-positive direct immunofluorescence test result. This outbreak is
therefore invalidated.
******
[2
CLASSICAL SWINE FEVER IN GERMANY
See also: 2 Nov 2001, 26 Oct 2001, 12 Oct 2001, 20 Jul 2001, 29 Jun 2001, 1
Sep 2000
(Date of last previously reported outbreak: July 2001).
Emergency report
Information received on 19 Oct 2001 from Prof. Dr Werner Zwingmann, Chief
Veterinary Officer, Ministry of Food, Agriculture and Forestry, Bonn:
Report date: 19 Oct 2001.
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 17 Oct 2001.
Outbreaks:
Location / No. of outbreaks
Bitburg-Pruem district, Rhineland-Palatinate (Rheinland-Pfalz) Land /1
Rhein-Hunsrueck district, Rhineland-Palatinate (Rheinland-Pfalz) Land / 1

Total number of animals in the outbreaks:
species / susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
sui / 2105 / 651 / 51 / 2054 / 0
Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: Rhineland-Palatinate Veterinary
Research Service, Koblenz.
B. Diagnostic tests used: direct immunofluorescence.
Epidemiology:
A. Source of agent / origin of infection: unknown. Investigations are in
progress.
B. Mode of spread: the fattening farm in Rhein-Hunsrueck received animals
from the breeding farm in Bitburg-Pruem.
Control measures:
- the remaining animals were slaughtered and will be destroyed in rendering
plants;
- prohibition on movements of animals of susceptible species in an area
around the infected holdings;
- tracing of animal movements into and out of the infected holdings.
******
[3
CLASSICAL SWINE FEVER IN GERMANY:
Follow-up report No. 1
See also: 26 Oct 2001, 26 Oct 2001, 12 Oct 2001, 20 Jul 2001, 29 Jun 2001,
1 Sep 2000
Information received on 31 Oct 2001 from Prof. Dr Werner Zwingmann, Chief
Veterinary Officer, Ministry of Food, Agriculture and Forestry, Bonn:
End of previous report period: 19 Oct 2001 (see Disease Information, 14
[43, 247, dated 26 Oct 2001).
End of this report period: 31 Oct 2001.
New outbreaks:
Location
Bitburg-Pruem district, Rhineland-Palatinate (Rheinland-Pfalz) Land
No. of outbreaks 1
Description of affected population in the new outbreak: breeding farm.
Total number of animals in the new outbreak:
species / susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
sui / 651 / 0 / 0 / 651 / 0
Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: Rhineland-Palatinate Veterinary
Research Service, Koblenz.
B. Diagnostic tests used: direct immunofluorescence.
Source of agent / origin of infection: contact with the breeding farm in
Bitburg-Pruem district mentioned in the emergency report.
Control measures:
- the remaining animals were slaughtered and will be destroyed in rendering
plants;
- prohibition on movements of animals of susceptible species in an area
around the infected holding;
- tracing of animal movements into and out of the infected holding.
